, ensemble methods and unsupervised learning techniques, such as clustering and dimensionality reduction. This book is suited for students who are interested in entering the field, by preparing them to master the standard tools in Machine Learning. The reader will be equipped to understand the main theoretical questions of the current research and to engage with the field.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aKernel-Methoden. 4aNeuronale Netze. 4aStatistisches Lernen. 4aüberwachtes Lernen. 7aMATHEMATICS / Applied.2bisacsh  aComplex analysis, analytic functions, complex integration, complex variables,.1 aGaston Ged, François, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut0 cEPUBz97831112898160 cprintz978311128847540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311128899440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111288994423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111288994/original  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles